public class DateCriteria
extends com.guidewire.pl.persistence.code.BeanBase
implements Versionable
    DateCriteria A component used as part of a larger search criteria entity. Encapsulates the information entered by the user to restrict the search to a particular date range. Specifies the date field to be restricted and allows the date range to be restricted either through a typelist of preset ranges (such as next 30 days) or through a start and end date.

    Very similar to DateCriterionChoice, but DateCriterionChoice supports configurable search. (See the Configuration Guide for details of customizing search screens.)
